<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>VIM VIEWPORT REFERENCE
======================
:sp         split window horizontally (:split)
:vsp        split window vertically   (:vsplit)

Ctrl-w      move between viewports

Ctrl-w j    move one viewport down
Ctrl-w k    move one viewport up
Ctrl-w h    move one viewport left
Ctrl-w l    move one viewport right

Ctrl-w =    resize viewports to be equal size

Ctrl-w -    reduce viewport by 1 line
Ctrl-w 20-  reduce viewport by 20 line

Ctrl-w +    increase viewport by 1 line
Ctrl-w 20+  increase viewport by 20 line

Ctrl-w &lt;    narrows viewport by 1 line
Ctrl-w 20&lt;  narrows viewport by 20 line

Ctrl-w &gt;    widens viewport by 1 line
Ctrl-w 20&gt;  widens viewport by 20 line

Ctrl-w q    close the active window

Ctrl-w r    rotate windows to the right
Ctrl-w R    rotate windows to the left

Ctrl-w o    the current window zooms into a full screen, or
            previous set of windows is restored.
            requires: ZoomWin plugin</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
<a href="http://puma.io/">Puma</a> and, to a lesser extent,
<a href="http://errtheblog.com/">Err the Blog</a>.</div></body></html>